  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> To answer a question on user groups, I just need to name some groups, like 'teenagers' or 'carers'.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Naming is only the first mark at most. The examiner is looking for you to link the group to what it NEEDS and WHY. Level 1 answer: \"A user group is teenagers.\" Full-marks answer: \"Teenagers are a user group who often need cheap, sociable sessions after school, because they usually have little money and want to take part with friends.\" The difference is the need and the reason.</p>",
  "question": "An 'Explain' question asks about the needs of one user group. What earns the marks?",
