  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> A very common mistake is mixing up which values belong to the Olympics and which belong to the Paralympics — for example, saying 'Courage' is an Olympic value.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Keep the two lists completely separate. Olympic values = Excellence, Friendship, Respect (three values). Paralympic values = Courage, Determination, Inspiration, Equality (four values). If your answer swaps a value between the two lists, it loses the mark even if the value itself is spelled correctly.</p>",
