  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> All three types of major event basically mean the same thing — they all just happen 'sometimes'.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> They are three distinct patterns, and the exam rewards telling them apart. The difference is entirely about the HOST LOCATION: a regular event repeats but moves host; a 'one-off' event barely repeats at all; a regular and recurring event repeats and stays at the same host. Saying an event 'happens sometimes' shows none of that understanding.</p>",
  "question": "What is the real difference between the three types of major sporting event?",
