  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> In an exam answer, just writing the correct type's name earns the same marks as explaining it.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Naming the type is usually only worth a mark on its own in the shortest 'Identify/State' questions. For anything asking you to Describe or Explain, you must pair the type with a correct, matching example or reason — the name alone is not enough to reach full marks.</p>",
