  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Any event with a big crowd inside the stadium counts as a 'major' international sporting event.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> A big local crowd is not the same as international scale. What defines a major event is competitors AND spectators being drawn from two or more different countries — including the much larger remote (TV/online) audience across the world, not just how full one venue looks on the day.</p>",
  "question": "What actually shows that a sporting event has reached 'major' international scale?",
