  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Objecting to a bid means you don't want your country to host any sport at all.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Objections are usually about priorities, not about opposing sport itself. Residents and pressure groups typically question whether the money spent chasing a bid is better used on other local or national needs, such as schools, hospitals or grassroots sport — not that sport shouldn't happen.</p>",
