  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> GPS trackers and video analysis are only used to measure fitness, never to improve technique.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> GPS data mainly tracks physical output (distance, speed, effort) so coaches can manage training load — but video analysis is used specifically to improve TECHNIQUE, by spotting faults a performer cannot feel themselves. The two tools do different jobs: one is about physical workload, the other about movement quality.</p>",
  "question": "What is the key difference between GPS data and video analysis in training?",
